---

<Layout title="Options">
  <h1>Global options</h1>
  <p>You can configure options globally by assigning an object to the variable <code>"window.UseBootstrapDialogOptions"</code>. For example:</p>
  <Code lang="typescript" code={exampleGlobalOptions} theme="one-dark-pro" />
  <p>Each method prioritizes object options followed by global options and lastly default options.</p>
  <h1 class="mt-5">Default options</h1>
  <p>Here are the default options for each method:</p>
  <Code lang="typescript" code={defaultOptions} theme="one-dark-pro" />
  <h1 class="mt-5">Available options</h1>
  <p>Here are the available options for each method:</p>
  <Code lang="typescript" code={availableOptions} theme="one-dark-pro" />
</Layout>
